      "diagnosis": {
        "failureClass": "CrashLoopBackOff",
        "rootCause": "The `checkout` container exits immediately on every start with \"FATAL: missing required flag --config\". The application requires a configuration file passed via a `--config` flag, but no ConfigMap (or equivalent config source) exists in the \"shop\" namespace to provide it. Without that configuration, the process terminates with exit code 1 on every attempt, causing a CrashLoopBackOff.",
        "suggestedFix": "1. Create the missing ConfigMap (e.g., `kubectl create configmap checkout -n shop --from-file=config.yaml=<path-to-config>`).\n2. Update the Deployment to mount the ConfigMap as a volume (or pass it as an env var) and add `--config /path/to/config.yaml` to the container's args/command.\n3. Verify the pod starts cleanly after the ConfigMap is in place.",
